Data available for ERE621

  • Using stem map data from Integrated Forest Study plots at Huntington, I want to find a way to predict tree positions across the whole mapped area from plot samples
  • Maps are 0.02 km2 (140 meters in both directions; 4.8 acres) and collected for 1985, 2000, and 2009
  • Interested both in recreating whole stem map from plot samples and in predicting future stem maps from past data
  • Interested both in spatial reasonability of outputs (K-function?) and in replicating distribution of marks (species and DBH)

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)

trees |> 
  select(Tag, EAST, NORTH, SPECIES, starts_with("CODE")) |> 
  tidyr::pivot_longer(-c(Tag, EAST, NORTH, SPECIES)) |> 
  filter(value == 1) |> 
  mutate(SPECIES = factor(SPECIES)) |> 
  ggplot(aes(EAST, NORTH, shape = SPECIES)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  scale_shape_manual(values = 1:16) + 
  facet_wrap(~name, ncol = 1) + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  theme(strip.background = element_blank(),
        legend.position = "bottom") + 
  coord_fixed() + 
  labs(x = "Longitude", y = "Latitude")

knitr::include_graphics("figure_1.png")
